{"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn about how to set up your project with the new authentication flow changes."}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/0210AuthFlowChange"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"anchor":"overview","level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"With the release of 0.26.0 comes a new migration flow for ATProtoKit developers. This change is fairly small, but this article will still cover what to expect in order to clear any confusion.","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Authentication Flow","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Authentication-Flow"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Previously, when you wanted to authenticate to an AT Protocol service, you used an initializer from ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":", which contained the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"handle"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"password","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" parameters. Then, you would use ATProtocolConfiguration.authenticate(authenticationFactorToken:) and passed the instance to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration(handle: example.bsky.social, password: hunter2)","","Task {","    do {","        \/\/ You can put it in here…","        try await config.authenticate()","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Or here…","        try await config.authenticate()","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"With version 0.26, this has been changed slightly:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let config = ATProtocolConfiguration()","","Task {","    do {","","        let atProto = ATProtoKit(sessionConfiguration: config)","","        \/\/ Enter the handle and password in here.","        try await config.authenticate(","            handle: example.bsky.social,","            password: hunter2","        )","    } catch {","        throw error","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Here are the changes being made:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"’s initializer no longer takes the "},{"code":"handle","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"password"},{"text":" parameters: now, ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)"},{"type":"text","text":" is responsible."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the only external change. However, more has been made internally:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSession"},{"type":"text","text":" is no longer stored inside of "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":": now, a new "},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" named "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/UserSessionRegistry"},{"text":" holds all instances of the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"struct"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UUID"},{"text":" value has been added to the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"text":". This value is linked to all objects that are related to the session. This is part of the new initializer for ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/init(pdsURL:keychainProtocol:configuration:canResolve:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"text":" now closely follows ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SessionConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":". In fact, the following methods are no longer stored in the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"class"},{"type":"text","text":", but have moved to default implementations of the "},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/getSession()","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/refreshSession()","isActive":true}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration\/deleteSession()"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"A new ","type":"text"},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", named "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","isActive":true},{"text":", will now manage the management of the password, access token, and refresh token. An ","type":"text"},{"code":"actor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", named ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is available for applications running on Apple’s platforms."}]}]}]},{"type":"heading","anchor":"SessionConfiguration","level":2,"text":"`SessionConfiguration`"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As mentioned previously, "},{"code":"SessionConfiguration","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" now has default configurations for each of the required methods. It is also "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Sendable"},{"type":"text","text":" and requires a "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to conform to it. The default implementation assumes you’re using an App Password to authenticate by default, but you’re able to create new implementations for your own conforming "},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Furthermore, the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/authenticate(with:password:)-272a8"},{"text":" method handles Two-Factor Authentication, but the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"protocol"},{"text":" can also handle OAuth. This is thanks to a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"AsyncStream"},{"text":"-related properties, named ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeContinuation"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"text":"Auto-managing the Keychain","anchor":"Auto-managing-the-Keychain","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As mentioned earlier, a new ","type":"text"},{"code":"protocol","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"type":"text","text":" have been made: "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" respectively. This manages the keychain items for the password and refresh token, as well as storing the access token in-memory."}]},{"type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The access token is being stored in-memory due to how frequently the token expires.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/AppleSecureKeychain","isActive":true},{"text":" conforms to ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SecureKeychainProtocol","isActive":true},{"text":" and is the default object used for Apple platforms. It’s also the default object used when initializing with ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtocolConfiguration"},{"type":"text","text":". However, you’re free to create your own implementation if it doesn’t suit your needs."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","style":"note","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"At this time, Linux and Windows developers will need to implement their own "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"code":"class","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to achieve the same effect. However, default ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"actor"},{"text":"s for those platforms will be created at a later date.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/atprotokit\/0210authflowchange"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"kind":"article","metadata":{"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","modules":[{"name":"ATProtoKit"}],"title":"0.21 to 0.26 Authentication Flow Migration"},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"references":{"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/ATProtoKit":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ATProtoKit"}],"title":"ATProtoKit","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/atprotokit","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The base class that handles the main functionality of the "},{"code":"ATProtoKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" API library."}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ATProtoKit","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/ATProtoKit"},"doc://ATProtoKit/documentation/ATProtoKit/SessionConfiguration/codeStream":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/ATProtoKit\/documentation\/ATProtoKit\/SessionConfiguration\/codeStream","url":"\/documentation\/atprotokit\/sessionconfiguration\/codestream","title":"codeStream","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The async stream that rece